snippet.description:

INSTAGRAM : - https://www.instagram.com/zakirkhan_208?igsh=MTBtNzVvNW1xOTYyag==
.
.

Get ready to laugh out loud with Zakir Khan in this stand-up comedy video where he dives into the rollercoaster ride of relationships! Zakir takes on the role of a funny relationship coach, sharing his hilarious tips and relatable stories about love's ups and downs. With his unique style of mixing humor with real-life advice, he makes understanding relationships a fun experience. So, sit back, relax, and enjoy as Zakir Khan shows us how to navigate the crazy world of love while keeping it lighthearted and entertaining!

snippet.title: Bachelors VS Society ‚öñÔ∏è - A Courtroom Drama | Baat Ka Batangad - E04 | Take A Break
snippet.description:
What happens when an entire housing society bands together against a group of carefree bachelors? Chaos, laughter, and a courtroom drama like no other! In Bachelors Vs Society, watch as tensions reach a boiling point when the society passes a new rule banning bachelors from the building. üè¢‚öñÔ∏è
Thrown out with all their belongings, the bachelors demand justice and call for a ‚Äúsociety court‚Äù to prove that they‚Äôve been unfairly targeted. What follows is a hilarious showdown where the bachelors present their side, exposing the society‚Äôs biases and poking fun at the stereotypes that surround them.

snippet.description:
Madha Gaja Raja is an upcoming Indian Tamil-language action comedy film directed by Sundar C and produced by Gemini Film Circuit. It stars Vishal, Anjali and Varalaxmi Sarathkumar in the leading roles, while Santhanam and Sonu Sood play other pivotal supporting roles. The film began production in 2012 and was completed by 2013, but remained unreleased for over a decade due to financial troubles. It is scheduled to release in theatres on 12 January 2025, during the Pongal weekend. Madha Gaja Raja pre release event happened in chennai today. Madha Gaja Raja public review will be out on Madha Gaja Raja FDFS. Presenting Vishal, Sundar C, Vijay Antony Interview about Madha Gaja Raja movie experience. snippet.title: CHICKEN 65 IDLI | Fried Chicken Idli Recipe Cooking In Village | Idli Cooking with Chicken Recipe
snippet.description:
n this video, we bring you a unique and mouthwatering recipe, Chicken 65 Idli!  A fusion of South Indian tradition and spicy flavors, this dish combines soft, fluffy idlis with crispy, flavorful fried chicken. Watch as we prepare this innovative recipe in our beautiful village setting, using fresh ingredients and traditional cooking methods.

What‚Äôs special about this recipe?

The perfect blend of soft idlis and spicy Chicken 65.
Simple steps that you can follow to recreate this dish at home.
A wholesome and flavorful meal for all occasions!
Join us for this delicious adventure filled with authentic village vibes.

Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta

Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani / Khushi Mali as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi 
Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi
Kush Shah as Gulabkumar Hansraj Hathi (Goli)
Shyam Pathak as Popatlal Pandey
Sharad Sankla as Abdul
Azhar Shaikh as Pinku 
Ghanshyam Nayak / Kiran Bhatt as Nattu Kaka
Tanmay Vekaria as Bagha

___________
In this Josh Talks video, meet Rahul Sinha from Bihar, the founder of the social media channel "Thethar Puns." Rahul has proven that difficult circumstances and financial struggles cannot stop anyone from achieving their dreams. With his hard work and unique approach, he made a name for himself on social media and won the hearts of millions.
Rahul's journey has been full of struggles. Born into a lower-middle-class family, Rahul took on the responsibility of his household by teaching tuition from the 10th grade. Due to financial constraints, he had to drop out of school. These challenging circumstances inspired Rahul to think differently. He started with network marketing but later moved to Mumbai to begin a new chapter in his career.
In the beginning, Rahul created content on several social media platforms, but he did not achieve much success. However, he didn‚Äôt give up and launched his YouTube channel "Thethar Puns" on May 28, 2020. He edited videos with speaking faces on inanimate objects like potatoes, onions, buckets, and motorcycles. This unique concept was loved by viewers, and soon his channel gained millions of views and subscribers.
Rahul's channel "Thethar Puns" has now earned a significant reputation. His YouTube channel has 8.85 million subscribers, and his Instagram has 3 million followers. His funny stories have earned him the YouTube Golden Play Button and opportunities like commentary in Bhojpuri for IPL 2024.

However, he didn‚Äôt give up and launched his YouTube channel "Thethar Puns" on May 28, 2020. He edited videos with speaking faces on inanimate objects like potatoes, onions, buckets, and motorcycles. This unique concept was loved by viewers, and soon his channel gained millions of views and subscribers.
Rahul's channel "Thethar Puns" has now earned a significant reputation. His YouTube channel has 8.85 million subscribers, and his Instagram has 3 million followers. His funny stories have earned him the YouTube Golden Play Button and opportunities like commentary in Bhojpuri for IPL 2024.

snippet.title: 3rd T20I | Highlights | Sri Lanka Tour Of New Zealand | 2nd January 2025
snippet.description:
In the 3rd T20I, Sri Lanka and New Zealand went head-to-head at the Saxton Oval. New Zealand won the toss and asked Sri Lanka to bat first. Sri Lanka posted 218 runs on the board for 5 wickets in their 20 overs. A brilliant 101 runs knock from Kusal Parera helped the Lankans to achieve a huge score. The Kiwis got a decent start and faught tooth and nail to achieve the target but fell short by 7 runs. Rachin Ravindra was the star player from the Kiwis team scoring 69 valuable runs.
.
